document_notes.text:
This update for oniguruma fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2019-13225: Fixed null-pointer dereference in match_at() in regexec.c (bsc#1141157).

notes.text: A NULL Pointer Dereference in match_at() in regexec.c in Oniguruma 6.9.2 allows attackers to potentially cause denial of service by providing a crafted regular expression. Oniguruma issues often affect Ruby, as well as common optional libraries for PHP and Rust.
